"""
adding Gaussing distribution to anti proton data array
"""

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statistics
from numpy import array
import pandas as pd
import random

data = []

"""
Read data from total data file
--------------------
"""
print("Reading data ...")
data = array(pd.read_table("/Users/jiancheng/CloudDocuments/Documents/Github/GRAMS/GRAMS_2021/output/TOF/TOF_anti_proton_1e5_0_500_45_4_result.txt"))
print("finish reading data!")

print(data[:, 0])
print(data[:, 1])
print(data[:, 2])
sigma = 0.3    #energy resolution percentage
deltaT = 0    #timing resolution/ns

time_pbar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))
dEOut_pbar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))
dEIn_pbar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))

for i in range(len(data[:,0])):
    dEOut_pbar_err[i] = random.gauss(data[i, 0], sigma * data[i, 0])
    dEIn_pbar_err[i] = random.gauss(data[i, 1], sigma * data[i, 1])
    time_pbar_err[i] = data[i, 2] + deltaT * 2 * (random.random() - 0.5)
    print("applying error:"+str(int(100*i/len(data[:,0])))+"%", end='\r')

plt.scatter(time_pbar_err, dEOut_pbar_err, marker = '.', color = 'b', label = 'TOF out layer')
plt.scatter(time_pbar_err, dEIn_pbar_err, marker = '.', color = 'r', label = 'TOF inner layer')
plt.title('anti proton TOF with error')
plt.xlabel('Time [ns]')
plt.ylabel('Energy diposit')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
#plt.axis([0, 20, 0, 10])
plt.grid(alpha = 0.2)
plt.show()

"""
adding Gaussing distribution to anti He3 data array
"""

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statistics
from numpy import array
import pandas as pd
import random

data = []

"""
Read data from total data file
--------------------
"""
print("Reading data ...")
data = array(pd.read_table("/Users/jiancheng/CloudDocuments/Documents/Github/GRAMS/GRAMS_2021/output/TOF/TOF_anti_He3_1e5_0_1500_45_4_result.txt"))
print("finish reading data!")

print(data[:, 0])
print(data[:, 1])
print(data[:, 2])
sigma = 0.3    #energy resolution percentage
deltaT = 0    #timing resolution/ns

time_He3bar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))
dEOut_He3bar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))
dEIn_He3bar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))

for i in range(len(data[:,0])):
    dEOut_He3bar_err[i] = random.gauss(data[i, 0], 0.3 * data[i, 0])
    dEIn_He3bar_err[i] = random.gauss(data[i, 1], 0.3 * data[i, 1])
    time_He3bar_err[i] = data[i, 2] + deltaT * 2 * (random.random() - 0.5)
    print("applying error:"+str(int(100*i/len(data[:,0])))+"%", end='\r')

plt.scatter(time_He3bar_err, dEOut_He3bar_err, marker = '.', color = 'b', label = 'TOF out layer')
plt.scatter(time_He3bar_err, dEIn_He3bar_err, marker = '.', color = 'r', label = 'TOF inner layer')
plt.title('anti He3 TOF with error')
plt.xlabel('Time [ns]')
plt.ylabel('Energy diposit')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
#plt.axis([0, 20, 0, 10])
plt.grid(alpha = 0.2)
plt.show()

"""
plot 3D comparison data
"""

from mpl_toolkits import mplot3d
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,10))
ax = plt.axes(projection='3d')

ax.scatter3D(dEOut_pbar_err, dEIn_pbar_err, time_pbar_err, marker = '.', color = 'royalblue', label = 'anti proton')
ax.scatter3D(dEOut_dbar_err, dEIn_dbar_err, time_dbar_err, marker = '.', color = 'lightcoral', label = 'anti deuteron')
ax.scatter3D(dEOut_He3bar_err, dEIn_He3bar_err, time_He3bar_err, marker = '.', color = 'limegreen', label = 'anti He3')


ax.set_xlabel("Out TOF dE [MeV]")
ax.set_ylabel('Inner TOF dE [MeV]')
ax.set_zlabel('time [ns]')
plt.legend()
plt.title("45 degree")
plt.savefig("./TOF3D.jpg")
plt.show()
